-- China's H-share index up 3 percent on stimulus hopes
-- By Alice Woodhouse
-- Mon Mar 24, 2014 02:36AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, March 24 (Reuters) - The China Enterprises Index <.HSCE> of mainland companies listed in Hong Kong extended gains on Monday, climbing more than 3 percent on expectations the Chinese government could unveil stimulus measures after a weak factory survey.

Short-covering by investors in the energy sector also lifted the index, with heavyweight Petrochina <0857.HK> <60857.SS> up 5 percent in Hong Kong.